1
00:00:01,068 --> 00:00:03,070
♪

2
00:00:04,104 --> 00:00:06,106
( Singing in Japanese )

3
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:27,828
Narrator:
Let’s rewind a little bit.

4
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:30,464
While Joseph and avdol
were battling Mariah,

5
00:00:30,497 --> 00:00:32,299
jotaro and polnareff were...

6
00:00:32,332 --> 00:00:34,734
( Children humming )

7
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:36,503
Girl: And here’s
your drink, ma’am,

8
00:00:36,537 --> 00:00:39,540
a super-duper tall glass of
whiskey and soda on the rocks.

9
00:00:39,573 --> 00:00:40,841
Enjoy.

10
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:42,676
Girl #2: It looks delicious.

11
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:46,613
Gulp-gulp, gulp-gulp,
gulp-gulp, gulp.

12
00:00:46,647 --> 00:00:49,550
Girl #1: Oh, my. Somebody’s
dying to quench her thirst

13
00:00:49,583 --> 00:00:51,118
early this morning.
Scandalous.

14
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:53,320
Girl #2: Darling,
how you do go on.

15
00:00:53,353 --> 00:00:55,655
My husband’s
gone away on a business trip

16
00:00:55,689 --> 00:00:58,158
and won’t return
for another week. ( Laughs )

17
00:00:58,192 --> 00:01:01,095
Girl #1: In that case, how about
enjoying a piece of cake?

18
00:01:01,128 --> 00:01:02,596
Girl #2: Oh, don’t trouble
yourself, dear.

19
00:01:02,629 --> 00:01:04,631
I’m quite all right. ( Laughs )

20
00:01:04,665 --> 00:01:06,133
( Polnareff laughs )

21
00:01:06,166 --> 00:01:08,468
Kids are great, huh?
So innocent.

22
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:10,537
Jotaro: Hey, it’s almost 9 A.M.

23
00:01:10,571 --> 00:01:15,409
( Sighs ) The old man and avdol
are taking way too long.

24
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:16,810
Polnareff: Mm.

25
00:01:16,844 --> 00:01:19,246
Jotaro: They may have had
a run-in with the enemy.

26
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:21,681
Polnareff: You think we should
see where they ran off to?

27
00:01:21,715 --> 00:01:23,617
Jotaro: I guess.
Ah, good grief.

28
00:01:23,650 --> 00:01:25,652
Polnareff:
It’s time to go, iggy.

29
00:01:25,686 --> 00:01:26,654
( Iggy groans )

30
00:01:26,687 --> 00:01:28,189
( Barks )

31
00:01:28,222 --> 00:01:30,191
Polnareff: Yeah, yeah,
I know you’re hungry.

32
00:01:30,224 --> 00:01:32,259
You’re not the only one,
believe me.

33
00:01:32,292 --> 00:01:33,827
( Iggy grumbles, barks )

34
00:01:33,861 --> 00:01:35,396
Polnareff: Hey, iggy,

35
00:01:35,429 --> 00:01:37,298
where in the world do
you think you’re going?

36
00:01:37,331 --> 00:01:38,732
Jeez, what a stupid mutt.

37
00:01:38,765 --> 00:01:40,367
- Jotaro: Let’s go.
- Polnareff: Hmm?

38
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,402
♪

39
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:46,773
Boy: Hey!

40
00:01:46,807 --> 00:01:49,910
Make some room, would you?
I wanna play, too!

41
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,446
Girl #2: No way we’d ever play
with a jerk like you.

42
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:53,747
- ( Girl #1 grunts )
- Boy: Oh, yeah?

43
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:54,914
You guys are the jerks around--

44
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:56,516
( girls gasp )

45
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:59,787
Boy: Ah, man,
that really hurt. Mm?

46
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:02,189
♪

47
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:04,224
( Mud dripping )

48
00:02:14,501 --> 00:02:16,269
Uh...

49
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:18,238
( Alessi sighs )

50
00:02:18,272 --> 00:02:21,408
Attaboy. You didn’t
shed a single tear.

51
00:02:21,441 --> 00:02:22,609
That’s impressive.

52
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:24,178
You sure you’re okay?

53
00:02:24,211 --> 00:02:25,546
Boy: Uh...

54
00:02:25,579 --> 00:02:28,348
Alessi: So, kid,
how old are you?

55
00:02:28,382 --> 00:02:30,251
Boy: Uh...

56
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:32,987
Alessi: Four years old, hmm?

57
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:35,389
Attaboy.

58
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:37,991
What about your daddy?
Where is he now?

59
00:02:39,026 --> 00:02:40,461
Boy: Uh, he’s at work.

60
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:41,829
Alessi: I see.

61
00:02:41,862 --> 00:02:45,299
So your daddy’s at work,
is he? Attaboy to you.

62
00:02:45,332 --> 00:02:47,267
And where’s your mommy?

63
00:02:47,301 --> 00:02:49,303
Boy: She’s at home
doing laundry.

64
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:51,238
Alessi: Attaboy.

65
00:02:51,271 --> 00:02:53,607
So you came here
all by yourself?

66
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,876
Boy: Mm-hmm.

67
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:57,978
Alessi: Good! Then there’s
no one around to stop me

68
00:02:58,011 --> 00:03:00,180
from bashing your face in
for ruining my pants!

69
00:03:00,214 --> 00:03:02,249
You gonna pay to get
the mud cleaned off?!

70
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:04,851
Or maybe you’re gonna get a job
for the cash to pay me back,

71
00:03:04,885 --> 00:03:07,388
because you think I have years
to wait for some little punk

72
00:03:07,421 --> 00:03:09,857
to work his way through debt!
You little shit stain!

73
00:03:09,890 --> 00:03:12,526
( Girls gasp )

74
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:13,760
( Alessi grunts )

75
00:03:13,794 --> 00:03:15,896
- ( Girls scream )
- ( Blows thump )

76
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:17,964
Boy: Mommy! ( Sobbing )

77
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:21,702
( Alessi scoffs )

78
00:03:21,735 --> 00:03:23,837
Joseph and avdol

79
00:03:23,871 --> 00:03:26,407
are in the middle
of doing battle with Mariah,

80
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,575
so I, alessi, shall take on

81
00:03:28,609 --> 00:03:31,579
the great honor
of killing jotaro and polnareff.

82
00:03:31,612 --> 00:03:33,414
They’re tenacious, to be sure,

83
00:03:33,447 --> 00:03:35,983
but i’ll do whatever it takes
to achieve victory.

84
00:03:36,016 --> 00:03:37,618
( Sighs )

85
00:03:37,651 --> 00:03:39,686
Attaboy, alessi.

86
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,656
( Laughs )

87
00:03:42,689 --> 00:03:44,524
Narrator: Enemy’s name--alessi.

88
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:48,395
Stand--set,
god of storms and chaos.

89
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:51,665
Favorite phrase--"attaboy."

90
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,069
♪

91
00:04:02,643 --> 00:04:05,279
Jotaro: Polnareff,
keep your guard up.

92
00:04:05,312 --> 00:04:07,848
Polnareff: Have you forgotten
who you’re talking to?

93
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:15,555
Hmm.

94
00:04:15,589 --> 00:04:18,058
Seems Mr. Joestar and avdol
already left,

95
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:21,428
and it doesn’t really look
like there was a struggle.

96
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:22,462
( Jotaro sighs )

97
00:04:24,665 --> 00:04:27,301
Old man, avdol, you here?

98
00:04:27,334 --> 00:04:28,669
( Sighs )

99
00:04:28,702 --> 00:04:30,037
Polnareff: Hey, jotaro,

100
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:32,773
i’m starting to get
a bad feeling about this.

101
00:04:32,806 --> 00:04:34,741
Jotaro: Me, too.

102
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:37,544
( Overlapping chatter )

103
00:04:45,385 --> 00:04:47,520
Woman: Ah, that looks yummy.

104
00:04:47,554 --> 00:04:48,955
Come on. Let me have a bite.

105
00:04:48,989 --> 00:04:51,458
Man: All right.
Just leave me some.

106
00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:53,126
( Iggy grunts )

107
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,795
( Barks )

108
00:04:54,828 --> 00:04:57,364
Man: Th-that dog
took my sandwich!

109
00:04:57,397 --> 00:05:00,133
Hey, get back here this instant,
you mangy flea bag!

110
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:04,972
♪

111
00:05:19,887 --> 00:05:22,423
( Metal clattering )

112
00:05:22,456 --> 00:05:23,657
( Iggy grunts )

113
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:25,659
Mariah: So you think
I have nowhere to go?

114
00:05:25,692 --> 00:05:29,029
You boys truly haven’t
realized it yet, have you?

115
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:30,897
You only thought
you were hunting me,

116
00:05:30,931 --> 00:05:33,600
when really I was luring you
here the entire time!

117
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:38,772
I’m afraid you’re going
to fry this time, joestar!

118
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:40,807
Avdol: Magician’s red!

119
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:42,776
( Magician’s red squawks )

120
00:05:42,809 --> 00:05:43,977
( Joseph groans )

121
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:45,980
Hermit purple!

122
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:47,982
( Groans )

123
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:50,384
Mariah: Avdol might be able
to defend himself for now

124
00:05:50,417 --> 00:05:54,521
with his flames, but not you.
Time to die, joestar.

125
00:05:54,555 --> 00:05:56,657
The goddess bast
is the perfect trap,

126
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:59,760
and it’s also far more powerful
than your hermit purple!

127
00:06:01,995 --> 00:06:03,697
( Overlapping chatter )

128
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:06,733
♪

129
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:08,935
( Bells jingle )

130
00:06:08,969 --> 00:06:10,904
Polnareff: Hmm?

131
00:06:22,049 --> 00:06:23,584
( Alessi gasps )

132
00:06:23,617 --> 00:06:26,186
Polnareff: Hmm.

133
00:06:27,955 --> 00:06:30,024
Alessi: Oh, dear,
that’s not good.

134
00:06:30,057 --> 00:06:31,926
I dropped my change.

135
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:34,962
Now, where’d it go?
Not over here.

136
00:06:34,995 --> 00:06:36,463
I’d lose my own head

137
00:06:36,497 --> 00:06:38,065
if it wasn’t attached
to my shoulders.

138
00:06:38,098 --> 00:06:40,834
Polnareff: Hey, what do you
think you’re doing?

139
00:06:40,868 --> 00:06:42,870
I can tell you’re following us.

140
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:44,872
( Alessi groans )

141
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:47,541
Polnareff: I can already see
the evil in your eyes,

142
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:48,975
so don’t lie. Got it?

143
00:06:49,009 --> 00:06:50,811
Alessi: Hmm? Hmm?

144
00:06:52,246 --> 00:06:54,548
I am so sorry, my good man.

145
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,116
Were you talking to me?

146
00:06:56,149 --> 00:06:59,819
I’m not sure I understand
what you meant by "evil eyes."

147
00:06:59,853 --> 00:07:03,690
My loving, non-evil parents
gave me these baby blues. Eh?

148
00:07:04,825 --> 00:07:05,959
Well, what do you know?

149
00:07:05,993 --> 00:07:07,595
It’s the change
I was looking for.

150
00:07:07,628 --> 00:07:09,797
Polnareff: Is that so?

151
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,598
Then prove it!

152
00:07:11,632 --> 00:07:14,668
It’ll be easy to prove
that you’re not a stand user,

153
00:07:14,701 --> 00:07:16,703
unless you really are one.

154
00:07:16,737 --> 00:07:17,938
Connard!

155
00:07:21,074 --> 00:07:22,842
( Gasps )

156
00:07:25,179 --> 00:07:28,049
Merde, that was a close one.

157
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:30,884
So I was right,
and you are a stand user!

158
00:07:33,921 --> 00:07:36,657
( Alessi scoffs )

159
00:07:38,058 --> 00:07:39,826
Polnareff: He’s running?

160
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:43,263
Hey, jotaro, it’s the enemy!
I’m hot on his trail!

161
00:07:43,297 --> 00:07:44,632
Jotaro: Hmm?

162
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,102
Polnareff.

163
00:07:48,135 --> 00:07:49,570
( Sighs )

164
00:07:49,603 --> 00:07:51,905
Polnareff, where did you go?

165
00:07:51,939 --> 00:07:53,808
Polnareff: Over here, jotaro!

166
00:07:53,841 --> 00:07:55,843
♪

167
00:08:00,047 --> 00:08:01,815
Come back here, damn you!

168
00:08:04,017 --> 00:08:05,585
( High-pitched )
Wait!

169
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:08,822
What the hell?!

170
00:08:08,856 --> 00:08:10,524
This guy is quick!

171
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:12,025
How can he be so fast?!

172
00:08:12,059 --> 00:08:15,696
Man, he’s already so far ahead.

173
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:17,030
Huh? That’s strange.

174
00:08:17,064 --> 00:08:18,566
What happened to my voice?

175
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:20,234
( Gasps )

176
00:08:22,269 --> 00:08:24,571
( Groans )

177
00:08:24,605 --> 00:08:25,940
Ow!

178
00:08:29,109 --> 00:08:31,678
( Gasping )

179
00:08:31,712 --> 00:08:34,114
W-what the heck is up
with my shoes?

180
00:08:34,147 --> 00:08:35,915
They’re ginormous.

181
00:08:35,949 --> 00:08:38,084
Man: Hey,
watch where you’re going.

182
00:08:38,118 --> 00:08:40,821
Don’t you know running around
in the street like that

183
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:42,155
can get you hurt or worse?

184
00:08:42,189 --> 00:08:44,291
You’re lucky
I wasn’t the front end

185
00:08:44,324 --> 00:08:45,559
of some out-of-control car.

186
00:08:45,592 --> 00:08:46,927
Polnareff: Shut up, idiot!

187
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,662
Why don’t you go
and lecture someone else

188
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:49,963
with that big mouth of yours?

189
00:08:49,997 --> 00:08:51,232
Now out of my way!

190
00:08:51,265 --> 00:08:53,901
I’m in the middle
of chasing someone!

191
00:08:53,934 --> 00:08:56,003
Hey! What do you think
you’re doin’?!

192
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:57,070
Let go of me!

193
00:08:57,104 --> 00:08:59,707
What? It’s really high up here!

194
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:01,875
He’s lifting me up
with one arm?

195
00:09:01,909 --> 00:09:03,744
Just how tall is this guy?!

196
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:06,780
His face and hands are huge.
It’s like he’s a giant!

197
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:09,082
Man: All right, listen here,
you pint-sized pissant!

198
00:09:09,116 --> 00:09:10,918
I’m gonna teach you
to go around

199
00:09:10,951 --> 00:09:13,987
shooting your ignorant little
mouth off to adults that way!

200
00:09:14,021 --> 00:09:15,055
( Slap thumps )

201
00:09:15,088 --> 00:09:17,257
( Polnareff groaning )

202
00:09:17,291 --> 00:09:19,226
Man: You think you’re a big man

203
00:09:19,259 --> 00:09:21,995
just because you’re playing
dress-up in adult clothes?

204
00:09:22,029 --> 00:09:24,798
Annoying,
good-for-nothing brat. Hmph.

205
00:09:24,832 --> 00:09:25,900
Polnareff: You bastard.

206
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:26,934
( Dog barks )

207
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:29,169
Agh! Wh-what the hell?!

208
00:09:29,203 --> 00:09:30,671
Cyclist: Move it, kid!

209
00:09:30,704 --> 00:09:32,606
- ( Bicycle bell rings )
- Get out of the way!

210
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:34,241
( Polnareff gasps )

211
00:09:34,274 --> 00:09:37,677
W-wait a minute.
What the hell is going on here?

212
00:09:37,711 --> 00:09:40,614
Why does everyone
look like giants?!

213
00:09:41,648 --> 00:09:43,750
( Gasps )

214
00:09:43,784 --> 00:09:44,818
What?!

215
00:09:46,186 --> 00:09:48,622
( Gasps )

216
00:09:48,655 --> 00:09:50,657
♪

217
00:09:58,999 --> 00:09:59,967
( Gasps )

218
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,669
W-w-what the--

219
00:10:02,703 --> 00:10:05,272
why am I a kid?!

220
00:10:05,305 --> 00:10:07,307
( Whimpers )

221
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:13,813
Is this really me?!

222
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:15,882
I’ve been turned into a kid!

223
00:10:15,916 --> 00:10:19,052
How is something like this
happening to me?!

224
00:10:21,421 --> 00:10:24,691
Polnareff: C-could this
really be happening to me?

225
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:27,595
There’s no possible way
this kid could really be--

226
00:10:27,628 --> 00:10:29,463
could really be me!

227
00:10:29,496 --> 00:10:31,565
Oh, my god, this kid is me!

228
00:10:31,598 --> 00:10:33,433
I turned into a little kid!

229
00:10:33,467 --> 00:10:35,302
( Laughs )

230
00:10:35,335 --> 00:10:39,506
No way! No way! No way! No way!

231
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:41,876
It must be his stand’s power.

232
00:10:41,909 --> 00:10:43,577
That creeper
must have found a way

233
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:45,879
to put a curse on me
during our fight earlier.

234
00:10:45,913 --> 00:10:47,915
I have a sneaking suspicion
it happened

235
00:10:47,948 --> 00:10:49,783
when his shadow stand
lunged at me.

236
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:52,385
How did I let him
do this to me?!

237
00:10:52,419 --> 00:10:53,754
Shit, this is bad!

238
00:10:53,787 --> 00:10:55,756
This is really bad!
What am I gonna do?!

239
00:10:55,789 --> 00:10:56,757
Eh?

240
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:57,858
Jo--

241
00:10:57,891 --> 00:10:58,859
jotaro: Hmm?

242
00:10:58,892 --> 00:11:01,762
Polnareff: Jo, uh--

243
00:11:01,795 --> 00:11:03,864
( jotaro groans )

244
00:11:03,897 --> 00:11:07,634
Polnareff: Uh, j-Jo--

245
00:11:07,668 --> 00:11:09,436
uh, n-no, Jay!

246
00:11:09,469 --> 00:11:11,438
Jackie! J--

247
00:11:11,471 --> 00:11:13,406
uh...

248
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,975
W-what was his name?

249
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:16,743
I can’t remember his name!

250
00:11:16,777 --> 00:11:18,646
But I know this guy.

251
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:19,914
He can help me!

252
00:11:19,947 --> 00:11:21,849
So why can’t I remember it?

253
00:11:21,882 --> 00:11:24,451
Why can’t I remember his name?!

254
00:11:24,484 --> 00:11:25,785
Jotaro: Hey, there, little boy,

255
00:11:25,819 --> 00:11:27,587
you, uh, didn’t happen to see

256
00:11:27,621 --> 00:11:29,690
a French guy come through here,
did you?

257
00:11:29,723 --> 00:11:31,658
This guy is about yea tall,

258
00:11:31,692 --> 00:11:34,528
and he’s got the exact
same haircut as you do.

259
00:11:34,561 --> 00:11:36,029
Polnareff: Yeah,
you’re talking about me!

260
00:11:36,063 --> 00:11:37,331
It’s me! It’s me!

261
00:11:37,364 --> 00:11:39,333
( Jotaro sighs )

262
00:11:39,366 --> 00:11:40,767
Ah, good grief.

263
00:11:40,801 --> 00:11:42,970
Asking a kid was an awful idea.

264
00:11:43,003 --> 00:11:44,838
Polnareff: Huh? Uh,

265
00:11:44,872 --> 00:11:47,308
hey, hold on!

266
00:11:47,341 --> 00:11:48,309
( Gasps )

267
00:11:48,342 --> 00:11:49,476
( Alessi laughs )

268
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:50,945
I take it you’ve realized

269
00:11:50,978 --> 00:11:53,447
that your body
has been changed into a kid’s.

270
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,449
Both your mind and your body
have regressed,

271
00:11:55,482 --> 00:11:57,217
and soon you’ll lose
all of the memories

272
00:11:57,251 --> 00:11:59,253
that you’ve built up
during adulthood.

273
00:11:59,286 --> 00:12:02,422
Polnareff: He can’t
seriously be able to erase

274
00:12:02,456 --> 00:12:04,625
everything I knew as an adult.

275
00:12:04,658 --> 00:12:06,994
( Gasping ) It’s true.

276
00:12:07,027 --> 00:12:08,896
It’s all becoming a blur.

277
00:12:08,929 --> 00:12:11,432
( Alessi laughs )

278
00:12:11,465 --> 00:12:13,300
Guess it’s about time, huh?

279
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:15,702
I love picking on the weak.

280
00:12:15,736 --> 00:12:17,705
It’s so amusing.

281
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:20,441
Attaboy, alessi. Attaboy.

282
00:12:22,442 --> 00:12:23,576
Uh-uh!

283
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:26,813
You’re not getting away,
you brat!

284
00:12:26,847 --> 00:12:29,817
( Laughs )

285
00:12:32,352 --> 00:12:34,487
I can’t say this too loudly,

286
00:12:34,521 --> 00:12:38,625
but picking on the weak really
gets me going, maybe too much.

287
00:12:38,659 --> 00:12:40,060
( Chuckles )

288
00:12:40,093 --> 00:12:42,395
I may be a bit sick in the head,

289
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:44,531
but, hey, c’est la vie.
Am I right?

290
00:12:44,565 --> 00:12:45,900
It’s like everyone says,

291
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:48,002
"if you think you’re
a little loony upstairs,

292
00:12:48,035 --> 00:12:50,538
then there’s a good chance
you’re probably not."

293
00:12:50,571 --> 00:12:53,340
It’s my confirmation
that i’m totally sane,

294
00:12:53,373 --> 00:12:55,275
and you can’t imagine
how good it feels

295
00:12:55,309 --> 00:12:57,411
to know that i’ll
never lose to some kid.

296
00:12:57,444 --> 00:12:58,645
( Polnareff gasps ) Mister!

297
00:12:58,679 --> 00:12:59,813
Whatever your name is,
you have--

298
00:12:59,847 --> 00:13:01,716
( groans )

299
00:13:01,748 --> 00:13:03,817
Jotaro: Hmm?

300
00:13:08,655 --> 00:13:09,723
Hmph.

301
00:13:11,692 --> 00:13:13,861
( Polnareff groaning )

302
00:13:14,928 --> 00:13:16,696
Alessi: As you no doubt know,

303
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:19,433
my mission is to wipe you and
your good-for-nothing cohorts

304
00:13:19,466 --> 00:13:20,701
from the face of the planet.

305
00:13:20,734 --> 00:13:22,369
Polnareff: Damn thing
won’t come off!

306
00:13:22,402 --> 00:13:23,436
Alessi: Unfortunately...

307
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:25,572
( Polnareff gasps )

308
00:13:25,606 --> 00:13:28,676
Alessi: I don’t have time
to savor the fun.

309
00:13:28,709 --> 00:13:31,078
( Polnareff whimpers )

310
00:13:31,111 --> 00:13:32,646
Alessi: Heh.

311
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:37,350
( Polnareff groans )

312
00:13:37,384 --> 00:13:38,852
Alessi: Huh?

313
00:13:41,588 --> 00:13:43,590
What do we have here?

314
00:13:43,624 --> 00:13:45,726
Silver chariot, eh?

315
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:47,794
I should have expected as much.

316
00:13:47,828 --> 00:13:50,631
Seems you were able
to summon your stand as a kid.

317
00:13:50,664 --> 00:13:51,798
But...

318
00:13:51,832 --> 00:13:53,500
Polnareff: Huh?!

319
00:13:53,534 --> 00:13:55,770
Just how strong
is this stupid stand user?!

320
00:13:55,802 --> 00:13:58,338
Even silver chariot is a kid!

321
00:13:58,372 --> 00:14:00,007
Silver chariot: Pami!

322
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,542
Pami!

323
00:14:01,575 --> 00:14:03,744
Polnareff: And he’s
just as weak as I am.

324
00:14:03,777 --> 00:14:06,046
He bent his sword
blocking those bullets!

325
00:14:06,079 --> 00:14:07,747
Alessi: My stand, set,

326
00:14:07,781 --> 00:14:09,616
reverted you back
to your childhood state,

327
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:11,552
which means that all
of your mental abilities

328
00:14:11,585 --> 00:14:13,353
were reverted
right along with you.

329
00:14:13,387 --> 00:14:16,790
Your stand has gone back to
a child’s stand, the form it had

330
00:14:16,823 --> 00:14:19,492
before you two were
fully attuned to each other!

331
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:22,129
( Laughs )

332
00:14:22,162 --> 00:14:23,830
Do you get it now?

333
00:14:25,165 --> 00:14:28,101
Good. It seems
like you understand.

334
00:14:28,135 --> 00:14:29,970
Alessi: Attaboy, kid.

335
00:14:30,003 --> 00:14:31,605
♪

336
00:14:34,474 --> 00:14:35,642
- ( Silver chariot whimpers )
- ( Polnareff whimpers )

337
00:14:35,676 --> 00:14:37,878
Alessi: But, as weak as it is,

338
00:14:37,911 --> 00:14:40,080
your stand
is still at your disposal,

339
00:14:40,113 --> 00:14:42,949
so I shall use my stand
for your execution.

340
00:14:42,983 --> 00:14:44,852
( Polnareff gasps )

341
00:14:47,087 --> 00:14:49,823
Alessi: Time to die, polnareff!

342
00:14:49,857 --> 00:14:51,692
You’re mine!

343
00:14:51,725 --> 00:14:53,794
Silver chariot and polnareff:
Oh, no!

344
00:14:54,995 --> 00:14:56,497
Polnareff: It broke in two!

345
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:58,732
( Alessi laughs )

346
00:14:58,765 --> 00:15:00,500
Eh?

347
00:15:00,534 --> 00:15:04,071
( Wails )

348
00:15:04,104 --> 00:15:05,739
Polnareff: Hurts, doesn’t it?!

349
00:15:05,772 --> 00:15:07,407
I meant to do that!

350
00:15:07,441 --> 00:15:10,644
Alessi: Ow! Ow! It hurts!

351
00:15:10,677 --> 00:15:12,679
( Wailing )

352
00:15:15,849 --> 00:15:17,584
( Polnareff gasps )

353
00:15:21,555 --> 00:15:23,490
( Woman gasps )

354
00:15:23,524 --> 00:15:25,860
Little boy, are you all right?

355
00:15:25,893 --> 00:15:27,128
Polnareff: Uh...

356
00:15:27,161 --> 00:15:29,196
H-he’s gone.

357
00:15:29,229 --> 00:15:31,565
So that guy runs for the hills

358
00:15:31,598 --> 00:15:34,134
as soon as there’s
another adult around.

359
00:15:34,168 --> 00:15:37,838
I’m safe for now, but that freak
was off his rocker.

360
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,242
Woman: Don’t run off,
little boy.

361
00:15:41,275 --> 00:15:42,843
Polnareff: Huh?

362
00:15:42,876 --> 00:15:44,811
Woman: It looks like
you’re hurt. What happened?

363
00:15:44,845 --> 00:15:46,513
Polnareff: Huh? I, uh--

364
00:15:46,547 --> 00:15:48,516
well, the thing is, you see--

365
00:15:48,549 --> 00:15:50,985
woman: What are
you mumbling about?

366
00:15:51,018 --> 00:15:52,653
Those wounds need to be treated.

367
00:15:52,686 --> 00:15:54,655
Why don’t you come with me
to my house,

368
00:15:54,688 --> 00:15:56,156
and i’ll fix you up, okay?

369
00:15:56,190 --> 00:15:59,527
( Polnareff gasping )

370
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:01,028
Should I go?

371
00:16:01,061 --> 00:16:02,796
If I don’t defeat
the stand user,

372
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:04,832
I won’t turn back into an adult.

373
00:16:04,865 --> 00:16:06,767
If the past is any indication,

374
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,136
he won’t attack me
with this lady around.

375
00:16:09,169 --> 00:16:12,506
I can use that time
to think of a plan.

376
00:16:12,539 --> 00:16:13,740
Woman: Come on. Hurry up.

377
00:16:13,774 --> 00:16:15,175
Polnareff: Whoa.

378
00:16:15,209 --> 00:16:17,111
Woman: Oh, that’s right.

379
00:16:17,144 --> 00:16:18,579
Polnareff: Huh?

380
00:16:18,612 --> 00:16:20,614
Woman: You’re hurt,
so climb on my back,

381
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:22,182
but make sure you hang on tight.

382
00:16:22,216 --> 00:16:23,551
Polnareff: Uh...

383
00:16:23,584 --> 00:16:24,585
( Chuckles )

384
00:16:26,153 --> 00:16:28,188
( Woman chuckles )

385
00:16:29,857 --> 00:16:30,991
( Polnareff sighs )

386
00:16:31,024 --> 00:16:33,093
She smells good.

387
00:16:34,161 --> 00:16:36,563
( Alessi gasping )

388
00:16:36,597 --> 00:16:39,733
This hurts like a bitch!

389
00:16:39,766 --> 00:16:42,068
Damn that little
crotch-sniffer!

390
00:16:42,102 --> 00:16:45,105
I’m not going to take this
from a snot-nosed kid!

391
00:16:45,138 --> 00:16:46,873
He’ll pay dearly for this.

392
00:16:46,907 --> 00:16:49,143
I swear i’ll butcher that brat!

393
00:17:03,657 --> 00:17:05,125
Polnareff:
From the looks of things,

394
00:17:05,158 --> 00:17:07,193
he doesn’t seem
to be coming after me.

395
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:09,730
Woman: All right, little boy.
We’re going to take a bath,

396
00:17:09,763 --> 00:17:11,231
so let’s take
those clothes off, shall we?

397
00:17:11,265 --> 00:17:12,767
Polnareff: Huh?!

398
00:17:12,799 --> 00:17:14,301
Woman: You’re completely
covered in grime.

399
00:17:14,334 --> 00:17:17,637
I’ll clean those wounds up
and put some medicine on you.

400
00:17:23,076 --> 00:17:25,045
( Polnareff gasping )

401
00:17:27,147 --> 00:17:29,049
( Laughs )

402
00:17:29,082 --> 00:17:32,052
♪

403
00:17:32,085 --> 00:17:34,154
Woman: What are you
staring at, sweetie?

404
00:17:34,188 --> 00:17:35,890
Take your clothes off.

405
00:17:35,923 --> 00:17:38,159
Better yet,
i’ll take them off for you.

406
00:17:38,192 --> 00:17:40,294
Here. Raise your leg.

407
00:17:40,327 --> 00:17:43,130
Polnareff: Hey, wait!
What are you doing, lady?!

408
00:17:43,163 --> 00:17:44,931
Woman: But what’s wrong?

409
00:17:44,965 --> 00:17:47,868
Polnareff: Uh, nothing at all.

410
00:17:47,901 --> 00:17:49,035
( Woman giggles )

411
00:17:49,069 --> 00:17:51,338
Polnareff: No, it is something.

412
00:17:51,371 --> 00:17:53,940
It most definitely is something.

413
00:17:53,974 --> 00:17:56,243
I don’t know why,
but I get the feeling

414
00:17:56,276 --> 00:17:59,079
that I should be really
embarrassed about all this.

415
00:17:59,112 --> 00:18:02,882
Wait. Oh, no. What if my--

416
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:05,552
agh! It’s so small!

417
00:18:05,586 --> 00:18:06,720
I don’t know why,

418
00:18:06,753 --> 00:18:08,922
but for some reason,
that makes me sad!

419
00:18:08,956 --> 00:18:10,090
( Crying )

420
00:18:10,123 --> 00:18:11,658
Woman: Hey, don’t cry.

421
00:18:11,692 --> 00:18:13,761
After we get
all that dirt off of you,

422
00:18:13,794 --> 00:18:16,096
you’ll be as good as new again.

423
00:18:16,129 --> 00:18:17,197
Here. Lift your leg.

424
00:18:17,231 --> 00:18:19,300
( Polnareff gasps )

425
00:18:22,269 --> 00:18:26,240
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

426
00:18:26,273 --> 00:18:29,710
I-i-i’m so happy!

427
00:18:29,743 --> 00:18:33,180
Are you positive it’s okay
for me to touch you like this?!

428
00:18:33,213 --> 00:18:34,948
Woman: Of course
it’s okay, silly.

429
00:18:34,982 --> 00:18:36,684
If we don’t
clean up those wounds...

430
00:18:36,717 --> 00:18:38,252
- ( Polnareff slobbering )
- They could get infected.

431
00:18:38,285 --> 00:18:41,889
Oh, you’ve got dirt
on your wee-wee, too.

432
00:18:41,922 --> 00:18:43,757
( Polnareff squeals )

433
00:18:43,790 --> 00:18:46,760
Oh, boy! I can’t explain why,

434
00:18:46,793 --> 00:18:48,395
but i’m just so happy
all of a sudden!

435
00:18:48,428 --> 00:18:51,164
I guess it’s all part
of being a kid.

436
00:18:51,198 --> 00:18:53,801
( Laughing )

437
00:18:58,772 --> 00:19:01,742
Woman: All right.
You be a good boy, okay?

438
00:19:01,775 --> 00:19:03,944
Polnareff: Okay! ( Laughing )

439
00:19:08,248 --> 00:19:10,283
♪

440
00:19:10,317 --> 00:19:12,052
Alessi: The fool’s delirious.

441
00:19:12,085 --> 00:19:14,654
Enjoy your stupor while you can,

442
00:19:14,688 --> 00:19:18,158
because i’m going
to chop your face in two!

443
00:19:18,192 --> 00:19:20,194
( Polnareff laughing )

444
00:19:24,798 --> 00:19:27,000
( Woman gasps )

445
00:19:27,034 --> 00:19:29,136
( Polnareff laughing )

446
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:30,737
( Woman chuckles )

447
00:19:30,771 --> 00:19:32,806
♪

448
00:19:35,008 --> 00:19:37,777
What could you be
grinning about, you silly boy?

449
00:19:37,811 --> 00:19:40,347
Now, I think it’s time
we wash your hair.

450
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:43,049
Polnareff: Huh?
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

451
00:19:43,083 --> 00:19:45,118
I hate using shampoo!

452
00:19:45,152 --> 00:19:46,420
( Woman chuckles )

453
00:19:46,453 --> 00:19:47,921
Polnareff: It gets into my eyes,

454
00:19:47,955 --> 00:19:48,956
- and I hate it!
- Woman: Rock-paper-scissors,

455
00:19:48,989 --> 00:19:50,390
- go!
- Polnareff: Scissors!

456
00:19:50,424 --> 00:19:52,026
Woman: Monkey, monkey, monkey,
monkey, monkey, monkey,

457
00:19:52,059 --> 00:19:54,161
both: Monkey, monkey do!

458
00:19:54,194 --> 00:19:55,462
Monkey, monkey do!

459
00:19:55,496 --> 00:19:57,898
( Polnareff groans ) I lost!

460
00:19:57,931 --> 00:19:59,132
( Crying )

461
00:19:59,166 --> 00:20:00,868
Woman: All right, sit still.

462
00:20:00,901 --> 00:20:02,970
( Bubbles popping )

463
00:20:03,003 --> 00:20:05,072
( Scrubbing )

464
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:09,844
( Polnareff groaning )

465
00:20:11,111 --> 00:20:12,913
Alessi: Does it sting?

466
00:20:12,946 --> 00:20:15,282
Polnareff: Yeah,
it stings a lot.

467
00:20:15,315 --> 00:20:18,151
Alessi: Can you wash your hair
all by yourself?

468
00:20:18,185 --> 00:20:20,320
Polnareff: Uh-huh,
but not as good as you.

469
00:20:20,354 --> 00:20:24,525
Alessi: Oh? Attaboy.

470
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:27,061
( Polnareff groans )

471
00:20:27,094 --> 00:20:30,497
( Alessi cackles )

472
00:20:30,531 --> 00:20:33,000
Yes, that’s the way, kiddo!

473
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,902
Attaboy!

474
00:20:34,935 --> 00:20:36,403
( Polnareff wails )

475
00:20:36,436 --> 00:20:39,005
That’s impossible!

476
00:20:40,407 --> 00:20:42,209
( Screams )

477
00:20:44,411 --> 00:20:46,413
♪

